observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed to:
a. ensure that timely and accurate RPT assessments are made through managing the factors affecting the availability of updated real property valuations by initiating, where practicable through its Sanggunian, the periodic revision of fair market values of real properties within the Municipality;
b. improve the collection efficiency by participating in the revenue setting process to come up with more realistic targets, employing effective strategies to optimally collect tax receivables, and avail the remedies set forth by the LGC in coordination with the PTO;
c. enhance its operating practices to further reinforce controls over its RPT and SET collections through institutionalizing measures that would ensure that RPT and SET collections are promptly remitted by collectors, and immediately deposited to an AGDB; and
d. enhance the reliability of its financial representation by instituting arrangements to ensure that RPT/SET are appropriately recognized in the year it was earned. To reclassify the prior years’ income and to correct the current year RPT and SET income accounts

